    Private Sub BtnCatTip1_Click(sender As Object, e As EventArgs) Handles BtnCatTip1.Click
        MessageBox.Show("⦁	Treatment options vary and depend on the type and " & vbCrLf &
                        "stage of cancer." & vbCrLf &
                        "⦁	Common treatments include surgery, chemotherapy, " & vbCrLf &
                        "radiation and immunotherapy or a combination of " & vbCrLf &
                        "therapies. Success of treatment depends on the form " & vbCrLf &
                        "and extent of the cancer and the aggressiveness of the " & vbCrLf &
                        "therapy. Of course, early detection is best." & vbCrLf &
                        "⦁	Some cat owners opt for no treatment of the cancer, in " & vbCrLf &
                        "which case palliative care, including pain relief, should " & vbCrLf &
                        "be considered. Regardless of how you proceed after a " & vbCrLf &
                        "diagnosis of cancer in your pet, it is very important to " & vbCrLf &
                        "consider his quality of life when making future " & vbCrLf &
                        "decisions." & vbCrLf &
                        "⦁	Some cancers can be cured, and almost all patients can " & vbCrLf &
                        "receive at least some benefit from treatment. Please note " & vbCrLf &
                        "that if your cat’s cancer is not curable, there are still " & vbCrLf &
                        "many things you can do to make your pet feel better. " & vbCrLf &
                        "Don’t hesitate to talk to your vet about your options. " & vbCrLf &
                        "And remember good nutrition and loving care can " & vbCrLf &
                        "greatly enhance your cat’s quality of life.")
    End Sub

